      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get the \"it depends\" thing, but if you look at history, doesn't it seem like the \"dangerous\" side is way more common? like, whenever people get super nationalist, it almost always ends in some kind of conflict or exclusion. isn't it kind of more accurate to say it's a fundamentally destabilizing force?",
